Aurora
======

SUMMARY

Aurora is a Perl based content delivery system, providing a modular
framework for dynamically repurposing XML content. Aurora includes
support for XML pipelines, XSP & XSLT transforms, session / connection
pooling and fine grain caching.


STRUCTURE

/server				 : The Aurora server
  /core				 : The core server & default components
  /components			 : Additional server components
    /aurora-plugin-authenticate  : Authentication plugin
    /aurora-serializer-xhtml2pdf : A PDF serializer
    /aurora-transformer-xsp      : An XSP transformer
/modules			 : Modules & tool dependancies for Aurora
  /aurora-httpd			 : A lightweight standalone HTTPD for Aurora
  /xml-object			 : A Perl datstructure to XML mapper
  /xml-sax2object		 : A SAX2 datastructure builder
  /xml-xsp			 : An XSP transformer
    /core			 : The core processor
    /taglibs			 : Additional XSP Taglibs


FURTHER INFORMATION

Further information regarding Aurora and its additional modules can be
found at:
 
   http://iterx.org/software/aurora
